name: The Forest
overview: In a small quiet village in the Ardennes, a sixteen-year-old girl disappears into the forest after calling her teacher in the middle of the night. Captain Gaspard Deker, a former soldier and newly arrived single father is conducting the investigation with Virginie Musso, the local cop. Also helping is the teacher, Eve Mendel, a solitary young woman with a mysterious past: she was found as a child by the villiage doctor wandering silently in the same forest.

episodes.name: Episode 1
episodes.overview: A newly-arrived police chief, Gaspard Decker, in the small village of Montfaucon begins investigating the disappearance of a 16-year old girl, Jennifer Lenoir.

episodes.name: Episode 2
episodes.overview: Captain Decker questions Maya, stoking tensions at the station. A grim discovery in the woods and two more disappearances put the town on edge.

episodes.name: Episode 3
episodes.overview: The police follow a tip to an Internet cafe frequented by the three girls. After uncovering a clue to her past, Eve seeks out Manoa for information.

episodes.name: Episode 4
episodes.overview: Virginie is emotionally wrecked as police investigation uncovers sordid secrets about her family. Eve searches the forest for more clues about her obscure past.

episodes.name: Episode 5
episodes.overview: Revelations about her past drag Eve even deeper onto the case. A witness excites Capitaine Decker's suspicion. The school falls victim to vandalism.

episodes.name: Episode 6
episodes.overview: The announcement of the identity of the murderer causes a feverish search. The families have to fight with the effects of the traumatic events.
